'''{{nihongo|Iinchō|委員長|}}''' is a [[Japanese language|Japanese]] term meaning Chairman.

In Japanese elementary school and junior high school, the class representative (''Gakkyū Iinchō'' or ''Gakkyūiin'') is commonly referred to by the shortened title "Iinchō".

In [[anime]], the class Iinchō is commonly depicted as a bespectacled girl (''[[meganekko]]'') and is often addressed by their classmates solely by their title rather than by their own name. Examples include:

*Yū Tobita in [[Gakuen Alice]]
*[[List of characters in Neon Genesis Evangelion#Other Child Candidate Hikari Horaki|Hikari Horaki]] in [[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]
*[[Characters of Negima#Class number 26~31|Ayaka Yukihiro]] in [[Negima]]
*Eimi Date in [[Pretty Sammy]]
*Ichijo from [[Pani Poni Dash]]

